sentences: Carl Emil Seashore, born Sjöstrand (January 28, 1866 – October 16, 1949) was a prominent American psychologist and educator.
He served as Dean of the Graduate College of University of Iowa from 1908–1937.

He emigrated with his family to the United States in 1870 at the age of 3 due to both economic and religious considerations and settled in Rockford, Iowa, before moving and settling in a farming community located in Boone County, Iowa.
He graduated from Gustavus Adolphus College in St. Peter, Minnesota, in 1891, having studied mathematics, music, classical languages and literature.
During his years in college he served as the organist and choir director of a local Swedish-American Lutheran church and his salary there paid most of his college expenses.
